    <text corresp="#c5663">
        <body>
            <div corresp="#c5663f1">
                <head>CANTON, China</head>
                <p>HISTORY (established, opened, closed, etc.)</p>
                <p>- CG closed 12/7/41 - CG est. 11/15/45</p>
                <p>Open to pub. 12/20/45 - CG closed to public 8/19/49 - Officially 8/24/49</p>
                <p>Opened 8/31/79.</p>
                <p>REMARKS: Cons. Dist: KwangTung Prov.-Macao (Portugese) serviced by Hongkong &amp;
                    Kwang-chow-wan (French)</p>
                <p>serviced by Saigon, Kwang-si; Hainan Is.; FuKien (5/16/49).</p>
                <p>PB MEMO NOS. 377</p>
                <p>DEPT.CONTACTS</p>
                <table>
                    <row role="label">
                        <cell>DATE</cell>
                        <cell>ACTION, COMMUNICATIONS, REMARKS, ETC.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>12/7/41</cell>
                        <cell>CG Closed upon declaration of war on U.S. by Japan. Final closings
                            12/8/41</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>7 a.m. Jap time. Non-conf. records, archives &amp; Govt.property
                            stored</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>locally. Prior to outbreak of war Conf. files placed in safe in CG's
                            office.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>(per old card files)</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>11/15.450</cell>
                        <cell>CG reestablished -- Opened to public 12/30/45</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </div>
            <div corresp="#c5663f2">
                <head>Canton</head>
                <table>
                    <row role="label">
                        <cell>Jan. 1949</cell>
                        <cell>Part of Embassy at Nanking moved to Canton. Address: TELCAN - tels.
                            from</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>5/16/49</cell>
                        <cell>Emb. at Canton--CANTEL Fukien Province trans'd from Shanghai Cons.
                            Dist. to Canton district, per instructions in DEPTEL 5/16/49</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>5/25/49</cell>
                        <cell>DEPTEL 1051 to Canton &amp; TELCAN authorize shipment inactive records
                            consigned to U.S.Despatch agent SFran via U.S.Navy for delivery Nat'l
                            Archives rep. at Naval Gun Factory, Wash., D.C.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>8/16/49</cell>
                        <cell>Tgm from Canton #2288 states Visa &amp; Citizenship services
                            discontinued today &amp; records being packed for shipment
                            HongKong.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>8/20/49</cell>
                        <cell>Tgm #299 from Canton states CG officially closed 5:30p.m. 8/19/49 but
                            maintaining skeleton staff time being services to US nat'ls and
                            finishing admin. matters. British CG instructed take custody property.
                            Records in Hongkong. Prin.officer and balance of staff will go Hongkong
                            about 8/22 or 23.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>8/25/49</cell>
                        <cell>DA-Mailing Notice 106 re closing to public 8/19/49 and expected final
                            closing 8/25/49. Telegrams temporary to office of Embassy
                            (TELCAN/CANTEL) GG, Hongkong</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>8/29/49</cell>
                        <cell>Unn.des. from Hongkong written aboard USS Dixie with detailed info re
                            closing. Attachment #1 memo with date of 8/24/49 that prin.officer &amp;
                            balance staff left Canton. Also Emb.unn.tgm from Hongkong 8/25/49</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>9/15/49</cell>
                        <cell>PB-Memo 377</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>10/10/49</cell>
                        <cell>Member of Embassy staff covering Canton from Hongkong</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>12/13/49</cell>
                        <cell>Post closed to Public 8/19/49 and Officially 8/24/49 DA-MN 154.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>3/25/50</cell>
                        <cell>- Tel. 619 from Hong Kong of March 25 - Delayed tel. from Brit.
                            Congen. Canton dated March 21 states auth. req. two US government-owned
                            buildings (MBK and YSB) immediately.Will telegraph when arrangements for
                            furniture, etc. completed. HK office Deacon and Co. received telephone
                            message their</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </div>
        </body>
